               <head>Pentateuch</head>
               
               
               
               <msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/n79066420" rend="visible">
                  
                  
                  
                  <summary>The Pentateuch, with vowel-points and accents, accompanied by masorah magna and parva, in two volumes.</summary>
                  
                  
                  
                  <textLang mainLang="he">Hebrew</textLang>
                  
                  
                  
                  <msItem rend="visible">
                     
                     
                     
                     <locus from="1v" to="151"/>
                     
                     
                     
                     <title xml:lang="he">תורה</title>
                     
                     
                     
                     <title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Torah</title>
                     
                     
                     
                     <note>
                        
                        
                        
                        <p>With vowel points, accents, Masorah Parva and Magna.</p>
                        
                        
                        
                        <p>With marginal notes.</p>
                        
                        
                        
                        <p>Volume 1 (Or 9885) contains Genesis (folios 1v-72v), Exodus (folios 72v-132v), and Leviticus 1:5 (folio 132v). Volume 2 (Or 9886) containing Leviticus 4:12 (folios 1r-44r), Numbers (folios 44r-101v), and Deuteronomy (folios 102r-132v). </p>
                        
                        
                        
                        <p>The verses from Leviticus 1:1-1:5, which appear at the head of part b, were supplemented by another hand. Parts of the manuscript were damaged and also supplemented by another hand.</p>
                     
                     
                     
                     </note>
                  
                  
                  
                  </msItem>
               
               
               
               </msContents>
               
               
               
               <physDesc rend="visible">
                  
                  
                  
                  <p>Paper codex of the 15th century.</p>
                  
                  
                  
