                     </supportDesc>
                     
                     
                     
                     <layoutDesc>
                        
                        
                        
                        <layout columns="1" ruledLines="20" writtenLines="20">
                           
                           
                           
                           <p>Uniform layout.</p>
                           
                           
                           
                           <p>Main text mostly in one column, surrounded with the masorah in the margin.</p>
                           
                           
                           
                           <p>Several leaves have been patched.</p>
                        
                        
                        
                        </layout>
                     
                     
                     
                     </layoutDesc>
                  
                  
                  
                  </objectDesc>
                  
                  
                  
                  <handDesc hands="1">
                     
                     
                     
                     <summary>Yemenite square script of the 15th century., punctuated Probably written by the same scribe as Oxford, Bodleian <ref target="http://digital.bodleian.ox.ac.uk/inquire/p/5a8ef1e0-ed08-4bbf-a4d1-1f1de5fa2f8c">MS. Oppenheim Add. 4° 97a</ref>. The latter was written by <persName>Yosef ben Benayah </persName>in 1478 (colophon on folio 315v).</summary>
                     
                     
                     
                     <handNote script="Hebrew" scope="sole">
                        
                        
                        
                        <p/>
                     
                     
                     
                     </handNote>
                  
                  
                  
                  </handDesc>
                  
                  
                  
                  <decoDesc>
                     
                     
                     
                     <decoNote>Masorah in a micrographical form.</decoNote>
                  
                  
                  
                  </decoDesc>
                  
                  
                  
                  <additions>
                     
                     
                     
                     <p>Missing, damaged parts are supplied by a later hand. His colophon is on folio 151v: נשלם תקון זה התאג’ .. שנת ב’ אלפים ומאה וארבעין שנין לשטרי במאתא כיואן .. והמתקן חתכי [=סאלם בא"ת ב"ש] בן כבוד אבא מנחם בן סעדיה.</p>
                  
                  
                  
                  </additions>
                  
                  
                  
